  "prompt": "What universities does W&T offshore recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "As of my latest information, W&T Offshore, like many energy companies, tends to recruit new graduates from universities with strong engineering, geosciences, and business programs. While specific universities and majors can vary, typical recruits often come from institutions known for their petroleum engineering, geology, mechanical engineering, chemical engineering, and finance/business administration programs. \n\nUniversities such as Texas A&M University, Louisiana State University, University of Texas at Austin, and other similar schools with well-regarded programs in these fields are usually top targets for recruitment. However, the specific universities and majors they focus on can evolve based on industry needs and recruitment strategies.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, I would recommend checking W&T Offshore\u2019s careers page or contacting their HR department directly.",
